BIODUN Stephens will return to cinema with her new feature film, Breaded Life. The new feature film will be screened to a selected audience on Saturday, April 10 at the Filmhouse cinema, Lekki. The new film, which is directed by Stephens is a collaboration between Shutterspeed Project and David Wade. It features leading acts like Jide Kosoko, Bimbo Ademoye, Timini Egbuson, Lateef Adedimeji, Bolanle Ninalowo, Bisola Aiyeola, Tina Mba, Nkechi Blessing, Funnybone, and MC Lively. ‘Breaded Life’ is the first project from Stephens in 2020 after directing Bisola Aiyeola’s debut film as a producer, The Kujus, in December 2020.